               <p>I am clerk to Mr. Foster, a <rs id="t17810530-16-viclabel60" type="occupation">coachmaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17810530-16-victim160 t17810530-16-viclabel60"></join> in Long Acre. He has a work-shop in <placeName id="t17810530-16-crimeloc61">Tottenham Court Road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17810530-16-crimeloc61" type="placeName" value="Tottenham Court Road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17810530-16-crimeloc61" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17810530-16-off58 t17810530-16-crimeloc61"></join>, facing Mr. Whitefield's chapel. I was, on a Thursday morning about eleven o'clock, in the compting-house: two sawyers were sharpening their saws; one of them came to me, and desired me to go over the way; I went; I saw the prisoner upon the top of the house: we surrounded the house; the prisoner was then at work; I called out, My lad, we 'spy you; he then put his legs through the trap-door, to come down; as he was coming down, I laid hold of his leg, and we secured him. We found 120 pound of lead cut off and rolled up; I went afterwards, and found some that he had thrown down.</p>
               <p>(
